author: Robert Baratheon

text: SPOILERS: Good movie but, as many pointed out, this borrows heavily from Heat. It has hotter adversaries and several different heist related angles though. I love that it was filmed in Atlanta (mostly). There were a few plot holes but some were required to make the film work. For example, I would have welded the manhole cover by the first bank shut. The time between leaving the bank to rolling up to the Federal Reserve was way too fast. I suspect that the Fed probably x-rays money carts at some point in the process but maybe not. I'm missing one or two others that I can't remember at the moment. Like I said, it couldn't be this movie had they no't existed. Just my  observations. All in all it's an enjoyable flick with some clever moves and good acting. B+ but A- minus if grading on a curve.

text: I waited for months for this film, the trailer is brilliant. The film very disappointing

I really can't help it but to comment on how epic of a failure this crap is. This film tries too much, it tries to be a captivating crime story,  heartbreaking drama,  cool heist movie and film with mind bending ending,  but it just subconsciously dugs a hole so deep beneath itself and falls into it crashing hard. It is one of those films that lie to you and try to outsmart you being always one step ahead of you ,but fail to realize how freaking dumb they got. Very trashy, derivative, messy, tiresome, bland with huge plot holes, stories that go nowhere and forgettable plot this is just tasteless fast food junk that you hope to get out of your system ASAP. 1/5
